# Cursor Rules (Project: "Google in a Day")

## Core language + typing
- Python version: Python 3.11+
- Strict type hints on all public functions.

## HTTP constraint (stdlib only)
- HTTP requests MUST use `urllib.request` from the Python standard library only.
- Forbidden: `requests`, `httpx`, `aiohttp`, `httplib2`, or any third-party HTTP library.
- Since `urllib` is synchronous, all HTTP calls MUST be offloaded via `loop.run_in_executor(None, ...)`.
- Executor threads MUST NOT read or write any shared state. They return plain data only:
  - `(html: str, final_url: str, status: int)`

## HTML parsing constraint (stdlib only)
- HTML parsing MUST use a subclass of `html.parser.HTMLParser` only.
- Forbidden: Beautiful Soup, `lxml`, Scrapy, PyQuery, or any other third-party HTML parser.
- Resolve relative URLs with `urllib.parse.urljoin`.
- Ignore non-HTTP/HTTPS schemes (`mailto:`, `javascript:`, `ftp:`).

## Concurrency model (hard rule)
- Use `asyncio` natively.
- Forbidden: `threading.Thread`, `multiprocessing`, or any non-async concurrency primitives.

## Asyncio boundary discipline (hard rule)
> All shared state lives on the event loop. All I/O lives in thread-pool executors. Never cross the boundary.
- Shared state MUST be event-loop-only:
  - `index`, `visited`, `metrics` (and queue bookkeeping) MUST only be read/written from asyncio event-loop coroutines.
- Executor isolation:
  - Executor threads MUST NOT touch shared state; they return plain values to the event loop.

## Back-pressure correctness
- Use `asyncio.Queue(maxsize=N)` (bounded).
- Enqueue MUST be non-blocking:
  - Use `put_nowait()` to enqueue.
  - Catch `asyncio.QueueFull`, drop the URL, and increment `dropped_count`.
- Never block on queue operations.

## Search correctness + fairness
- Search runs while crawling continues; search reads from the live `index` on the event loop thread.
- For large indexes (> 5000 entries), periodically yield to avoid starving crawler coroutines:
  - every ~500 scanned entries, do `await asyncio.sleep(0)`.

## Frontend constraint
- React implementation MUST use functional components and hooks only.
- No class components.

## API constraint
- Backend MUST be FastAPI.
- Metrics MUST stream via WebSocket on `/ws/metrics`.

## Debug / QA
- System MUST run cleanly under `PYTHONASYNCIODEBUG=1`.
